This fixture is a small Cargo package for read-only feature-suite integration
coverage against rust-analyzer. The source is intentionally not rustfmt-formatted
so formatting previews return edits without mutating files.

Markers embedded in the source drive the test:

  hover=ANSWER    marks the constant queried by textDocument/hover.
  rename=message  marks the function declaration queried by textDocument/rename.
  query=message   marks a function reference that should be renamed too.

-- Cargo.toml --
[package]
name = "mcp_lsp_rust_feature_fixture"
version = "0.1.0"
edition = "2024"

[dependencies]
-- src/main.rs --
const ANSWER:i32=42; // hover=ANSWER

fn message(name:&str)->String { // rename=message
format!("hello {name} {ANSWER}")
}

fn main(){
println!("{}",message("rustacean")); // query=message
}
